SYMPTOM

User forgot their password after returning from a two-week vacation and is unable to sign in to their account.

ISOLATION

Troubleshooting performed:

Confirmed the user could not remember their password.
Verified the user's identity according to company policy.
Confirmed with the user's manager that a password reset was authorized.
Determined there were no account lockout or system outage issues.
ROOT CAUSE

The user forgot their password after an extended period away from work. No technical fault was identified.

FIX
Verified the user's identity.
Reset the user's password in Active Directory.
Assigned a temporary password.
Instructed the user to sign in and change the temporary password to a new secure password at first login.
VERIFICATION

User successfully signed in using the temporary password, created a new password, and confirmed access to email, Teams, and other company resources before their scheduled meetings.

PREVENTION
Encourage users to use the company's approved password manager if one is available.
Enroll users in Self-Service Password Reset (SSPR) where supported.
Avoid writing passwords in Notepad or other unsecured locations.
